ore motivated students, more compassionate students and thus you will learn more.  Yes public schools have these students as well but they are also saddled with a much larger percent of behavior problems, plenty of kids with a total lack of interest in learning who have parents that are the same way.  What does this produce?  Usually a school where tons of money and energy are spent trying to get this bottom 15% to care and learn while they disrupt and vandalize their way through school ruining the learning experience for the ones who do care. My granddaughters go to a type of charter school that you must apply for and qualify for. They have uniforms for all students and the focus on education is fantastic.  If you don't like the rules or fail to achieve at a certain level you are back in the regular public school where you can carry on as you like.  Tell me which school no matter what your color is you will learn more in. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1244" language="en" documentId="3657" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="harrier60" date="Aug 29, 2013 6:49PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="4" thumbsDown="0" origId="3657" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1244"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>